The paper focuses on unsupervised visual representation learning using convolutional neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of neural networks for this task also falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of natural language processing techniques for evaluating the learned representation, which falls under computational linguistics (cs.CL). Finally, the paper uses a specific type of neural network architecture, which is a feedforward neural network, falling under neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
